## ✅ SHOPIFY CUSTOMISER REQUIREMENTS

Every section MUST be fully editable in Shopify Theme Customiser:
- All text → `type: "text"` or `type: "richtext"` settings
- All colors → `type: "color"` settings with brand defaults
- All images → `type: "image_picker"` settings
- Show/hide toggles → `type: "checkbox"` settings
- Collection pickers → `type: "collection"` settings
- Number inputs for limits → `type: "range"` settings

Schema example for every section:
```json
{
  "name": "Section Name",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "text", "id": "heading", "label": "Heading", "default": "Default Text" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "bg_color", "label": "Background Color", "default": "#fdf7f5" },
    { "type": "checkbox", "id": "show_section", "label": "Show section", "default": true }
  ],
  "presets": [{ "name": "Section Name" }]
}
```

---

## 🚫 NEVER DO THESE

- Never use `!important` in CSS
- Never hardcode product titles or prices — always use Liquid variables
- Never use `document.write()`
- Never use inline `style=""` for brand colors — use CSS variables
- Never create sections without a `{% schema %}` block
- Never use external CDN libraries (Shopify theme = no CDN access in liquid)
- Never break mobile responsiveness
- Never use `alert()` or `console.error()` in production code
- Never write animations that animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin` (causes layout reflow)

---

